FuncDef: This command changes the edit point of the candidate configuration. The edit point is the point after which new commands are inserted into the candidate configuration as an operator navigates the CLI and issues commands in edit-cfg mode.

ParaDef.Info: Indicates which line to change starting at the point indicated by the following options. Values-line, offset, first, edit-point, last, |line |absolute line number, |offset|relative line number to current edit point. Prefixed with '+' or '-', |first |keyword - first line, |edit-point |keyword - current edit point , |last |keyword - last line that is not 'exit'.
